githubGet[source]

githubGet(url:str, token:str)

get request to github using token parameters: url:str: github raw file url token:str: your personal access token response: response: requests.Response: response object

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thanakijwanavit/villaConfig/main/cloudsearch.yaml'
githubGet(url, token).text

'# details about parameter in python https://boto3.amazonaws.com/v1/documentation/api/latest/reference/services/cloudsearchdomain.html#CloudSearchDomain.Client.search\n# searching guide https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cloudsearch/latest/developerguide/searching.html\nsearchParams:\n  expr: ""\n  facet: ""\n  filterQuery: ""\n  highlight: ""\n  queryOptions: ""\n  queryParser: ""\n  returnFields: ""\n  size: 100\n  sort: ""\n'
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

githubGetYaml[source]

githubGetYaml(url:str, token:str)

get yaml dictionary from github using token parameters: url:str: github raw file url token:str: your personal access token response: response: dict: yaml dictionary

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thanakijwanavit/villaConfig/main/cloudsearch.yaml'
githubGetYaml(url, token)

{'searchParams': {'expr': '',
  'facet': '',
  'filterQuery': '',
  'highlight': '',
  'queryOptions': '',
  'queryParser': '',
  'returnFields': '',
  'size': 100,
  'sort': ''}}
{% endraw %}
